The paper focuses on regularization techniques for machine learning models, specifically label smoothing for neural networks. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper primarily deals with neural networks and their regularization, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant but to a lesser extent.
